column2: sunny- air in the 40s- not much wind
sunny with some clouds--moderate wind--lots of filamentous algae noticeable--big difference in water column temp: 47.3 at 20 ft; 62.4 at surface
sunny with slight wind--trained new volunteer- Steve Brill--shallow end of lakes has algae clumps- like many lakes in county from still hot weather
Calm + Cloudy.  Heavy rain from about 2:00 A.M. to 6:00 A.M. on 8/25/14.
windy and sunny--no sign of aquatic plant growth--air temp 58.1 F
Mostly sunny.  Winds are 8 mph from East.  Temperature about 70 degrees.
Mostly Sunny.  Winds are 12mph from NW.  Temperature about 77 degrees.
Sunny.  Winds are 0-5 mph from N.  Temperature about 63 degrees.  Heavy rains on 9/8/15.  Lake has been unusually weedy most of the summer.
cold- very overcast--little plant growth seen except Northern Milfoil and Chara--looked near shore around lake for Curly-Leaf Pondweed but found only a couple of small spots (using rake + visual)
Mostly Sunny- Winds are 13mph from the West- Temperature is 81 degrees. Mostly Sunny- Winds are 13mph from the West- Temperature is 81 degrees
Mostly Sunny- Winds are 7mph from the NW- Temperature is 73 degrees. Mostly Sunny- Winds are 7mph from NW- Temperature is 73 degrees.
Mostly Sunny- Winds are 4mph from WSW- Temperature is 77 degrees.
Temperature was 66 degrees- Wind was 7-10 mph from the West and it was mostly sunny.
Temperature was 66 degrees- Wind was 8 mph from the NNE- and it was mostly cloudy.
Temperature was 72 degrees- Wind was 4 mph from the SSE- and it was mostly cloudy.  There was an unusually high amount of weeds on the north lobe of the lake.
Overcast- Winds at 4 mph SSE- Temperature was 71 degrees. Overcast- Winds at 4 mph SSE- Temperature was 71 degrees.
Sky is clear- winds are 6 mph (N)- and Temperature is 74 degrees.  The channel and north lobe of the lake have more weeds than normal and there is a lot of algae in these parts of the lake.
Overcast- Winds 7 mph E- and temperature is 72 degrees.  There is an unusually high amount of weeds and algae on the North Lobe of the lake.
